        <div class="logo">ü•ó</div>
        <h1>Account Deletion Request</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Ingredly App</p>
      </header>

      <p>
        We understand that you may want to delete your Ingredly account and
        associated data. This page outlines the process and what happens when
        you request account deletion.
      </p>

      <h2>How to Request Account Deletion</h2>

      <h3>Option 1: In-App Deletion (Recommended)</h3>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>
          <strong>Open the Ingredly app</strong> on your device
        </li>
        <li>
          Navigate to <strong>Profile ‚Üí Settings</strong>
        </li>
        <li>
          Scroll down and tap <strong>"Delete Account"</strong>
        </li>
        <li>
          Confirm your decision by entering your password
        </li>
        <li>
          Your account and data will be permanently deleted immediately
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Option 2: Email Request</h3>
      <p>
        If you're unable to access the app, you can request account deletion by
        contacting us:
      </p>

      <div class="contact-box">
        <h3>üìß Contact Us for Account Deletion</h3>
        <p>Send an email to:</p>
        <a href="mailto:support@ingredly.com?subject=Account%20Deletion%20Request&body=Please%20delete%20my%20account%20and%20all%20associated%20data.%0A%0AEmail%3A%20%5Byour%20registered%20email%5D%0AName%3A%20%5Byour%20name%5D">
          support@ingredly.com
        </a>
        <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 0.9em;">
          Include your registered email address and confirm you want your
          account deleted
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>
        <strong>Subject:</strong> Account Deletion Request<br />
        <strong>Include:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your registered email address</li>
        <li>Your full name (as registered in the app)</li>
        <li>Confirmation that you want to delete your account and all data</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        We will process your request within <strong>7 business days</strong> and
        send you a confirmation email once completed.
      </p>

      <div class="warning-box">
        <h3>‚ö†Ô∏è Important: What Gets Deleted</h3>
        <p>
          When you delete your account, the following data will be
          <strong>permanently removed</strong> and cannot be recovered:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Email, name, password</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Profile Data:</strong> Dietary preferences, allergen
            information, health goals, age, gender, height, weight, activity
            level
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Scan History:</strong> All food scans and nutrition analyses
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Meal Tracking:</strong> Complete meal history and nutrition
            logs
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Images:</strong> All uploaded food and label images
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Subscription Data:</strong> Subscription status and payment
            history (Note: active subscriptions must be cancelled separately
            through Google Play Store or Apple App Store)
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2>Data Retention Details</h2>

      <table class="data-retention-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Data Type</th>
            <th>Action Taken</th>
            <th>Retention Period</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Account Information</td>
            <td>Permanently Deleted</td>
            <td>Immediate</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Profile & Health Data</td>
            <td>Permanently Deleted</td>
            <td>Immediate</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Scan & Meal History</td>
            <td>Permanently Deleted</td>
            <td>Immediate</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Uploaded Images</td>
            <td>Permanently Deleted</td>
            <td>Immediate</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Transaction Records</td>
            <td>Anonymized</td>
            <td>7 years (tax/legal compliance)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Support Tickets</td>
            <td>Anonymized</td>
            <td>2 years (quality assurance)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="info-box">
        <h3>üí° Legal & Financial Data Retention</h3>
        <p>
          Due to legal and regulatory requirements, we must retain certain
          financial records:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Transaction/Payment Records:</strong> Kept for 7 years in an
            anonymized form for tax compliance and financial auditing
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Support Communications:</strong> Anonymized and retained for
            up to 2 years for quality assurance purposes
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These records are completely anonymized (your personal identifiers are
          removed) and cannot be linked back to you.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2>Cancelling Active Subscriptions</h2>

      <p>
        <strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Deleting your account does not automatically
        cancel active subscriptions. You must cancel your subscription
        separately:
      </p>

      <h3>For Google Play Store (Android):</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the Google Play Store app</li>
        <li>Tap your profile icon ‚Üí Payments & subscriptions ‚Üí Subscriptions</li>
        <li>Find "Ingredly" and tap Cancel subscription</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>For Apple App Store (iOS):</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Open Settings ‚Üí [Your Name] ‚Üí Subscriptions</li>
        <li>Find "Ingredly" and tap Cancel Subscription</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Alternative: Data Deletion Without Account Deletion</h2>

      <p>
        If you want to keep your account but delete specific data (e.g., meal
        history, scans), you can do so through the app:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Delete individual meals:</strong> Swipe left on any meal entry
          ‚Üí Delete
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Clear scan history:</strong> Profile ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Clear Scan
          History
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Update profile data:</strong> Profile ‚Üí Edit Profile
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        For partial data deletion requests, please contact us at
        <a href="mailto:support@ingredly.com" class="email-link"
          >support@ingredly.com</a
        >
      </p>

